Tammy Petersen, News24FILE (ER24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Pietermaritzburg - A three-week old baby was among those injured in a midnight crash on the N3 in Pietermaritzburg which claimed the lives of three people.Netcare 911 spokesperson says the paramedics and other emergency services responded to the &ldquo;horrific&rdquo; scene on the N3 North at the New England Road off ramp just before 00:00.&ldquo;Reports from the scene indicate that an errant party had crossed the centre median and collided head-on with another vehicle travelling in the opposite direction,&rdquo; he said.&ldquo;Paramedics arrived at the scene and found accident debris and the twisted frames of the vehicles, consistent with that of a high impact collision, spread over the highway. After the injured were examined, it was found that three people tragically died, one was in a critical condition, while two others sustained seriously injured. One of the seriously injured was a three-week-old baby.&rdquo;Various paramedics stabilised the injured before transporting them to hospital.Authorities are investigating. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.